text: "True statement about Iron Isomaltoside 1000 is:",
options: [{"id": "A", "text": "Iron requirement can be fulfilled in single dose", "is_correct": true}, {"id": "B", "text": "More immunogenic than iron dextran", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "C", "text": "Given intravenously and gets deposited in adipose tissue therefore less toxic", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "D", "text": "Best when given with erythropoietin", "is_correct": false}],
explanation: "Iron isomaltoside 1000 (ferric derisomaltose) is a modern intravenous iron preparation that allows total iron replacement in a single high-dose infusion due to its stable iron\u2013carbohydrate complex.\nKey features:<br><br>* Can deliver full iron requirement in one sitting (single total-dose infusion)\n* Low risk of free iron release \u2192 fewer infusion reactions\n* Less immunogenic than older preparations like high\u2013molecular-weight iron dextran\n* Used in iron deficiency anemia when rapid repletion is required or oral iron is not tolerated",
