tags: ["Path_Images"],
text: "A 3-year-old boy is brought to the physician with jaundice and pallor. He was adopted and his family history is unknown. Laboratory studies show anemia, reticulocytosis, and increased indirect bilirubin. A peripheral blood smear is shown. This patient is most likely to have which of the following additional findings?",
options: [{"id": "A", "text": "Decreased lactate dehydrogenase", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "B", "text": "Increased haptoglobin", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "C", "text": "Increased MCHC", "is_correct": true}, {"id": "D", "text": "Positive Coombs test", "is_correct": false}],
explanation: "Hereditary spherocytosis is a hemolytic anemia due to defects in RBC membrane proteins (spectrin, ankyrin, band 3), causing formation of spherocytes that are trapped and destroyed in the spleen.<br><br>Key laboratory features:<br><br>* Increased MCHC (hallmark finding)\n* Reticulocytosis\n* \u2191 Indirect bilirubin\n* \u2191 LDH\n* \u2193 Haptoglobin\n* Negative Coombs test<br><br>Peripheral smear: spherocytes without central pallor.",
